            <h1>Cause</h1>

            <p>
                A variety of diseases and conditions can cause damage to the aorta and put patients at great, life-threatening risk. Those conditions include:
                Atherosclerosis (hardening of the arteries); Hypertension (high blood pressure); Genetic conditions (such as Marfan Syndrome); Connective tissue disorders (such as Ehler-Danlos disorder, polychondritis, scleroderma, osteogenesis imperfecta, polycystic kidney disease and Turners Syndrome); Injury.
            </p>
