            <h1>Symptoms</h1>
            <p>
                Thoracic aortic aneurysms often grow slowly and usually without symptoms, making them difficult to detect. Some aneurysms will never rupture. Many start small and stay small, although many expand over time. How quickly an aortic aneurysm may grow is difficult to predict.            </p>
            <p>
                As a thoracic aortic aneurysm grows, some people may notice:

                Tenderness or pain in the chest; Back pain; Hoarseness; Cough; Shortness of breath
            </p>
